Package nl.pim16aap2.animatedarchitecture.core.structures.properties

Class PropertyContainer

java.lang.Object
nl.pim16aap2.animatedarchitecture.core.structures.properties.PropertyContainer
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<PropertyValuePair<?>>, IPropertyContainerConst, IPropertyHolder, IPropertyHolderConst
@NotThreadSafe public final class PropertyContainer extends Object implements IPropertyHolder, IPropertyContainerConst
Manages the properties of a structure.

New instances of this class can be created using forType(StructureType).

A property container is created for a specific structure type. It contains all properties that are defined for that type as defined by StructureType.getProperties().

It is not possible to set a property that is not defined for the structure type this property container was created for. Attempting to do so will result in an IllegalArgumentException.

    • of

      public static PropertyContainer of(@Nullable @Nullable Object @Nullable ... properties)
      Creates a new PropertyContainer from the given properties.
      Parameters:
      properties - A group of interleaved property-value pairs.

      The even indices must be non-null Propertys.

      The odd indices are the (nullable) values for the properties.

      Returns:
      A new PropertyContainer with the given properties.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If the properties are not provided in pairs of 2.

      If an object at an even index is not a Property.

      NullPointerException - If a property is null.
      ClassCastException - If the value of a property cannot be cast to the type of the preceding property using Property.cast(Object).
